text: Luis Garrido (born 1990), Honduran football player. Luis Garrido may also refer to: ==Politics== *Luis B. Garrido Ampuero, Chilean politician, governor of El Loa *Luis Garrido Juaristi in list of mayors of Madrid (1918–1920) *Luis Javier Garrido (1941–2012), Mexican political analyst ==Others== *Luis Garrido (sport shooter), Puerto Rican shooter in shooting at the 1988 Summer Olympics – Trap *Luis Fernando Garrido, Colombian discus thrower in 1983 South American Junior Championships in Athletics and athletics at the 1989 Bolivarian Games *Luis de Garrido (born 1967), Spanish architect *José Luis Garrido, got 20th Goya Awards for best original score in 2006 *Juan Luis Suárez Garrido, Spanish guitarist of El Sueño de Morfeo *Luis Ramón Garrido, Mexican badminton player
title: Luis Garrido (disambiguation)
